column5: Gas just Spiked up 6 cents in Saskatoon without reason.  Here we go again.  Does anybody have an explanation or at least an excuse.  All I know it seems when I read something in Yahoo dealing with gas it goes up.  Its like advertising an excuse.  So now its 89.9 cents and I think less than forty a Barrel
Why? Crude is down under $35 a barrel. If anything it should still be dropping.
thats what I was thinking also!   A  5 year low and Gas goes up...weird!!!
i filled up at 77.9 this afternoon
I believe they have cut production...
didn't look at it this morning, put the nozzle in the sierra and it clicked off at 68 bones
It will be $200/barrel in two years..so start savin' yer empties.
ha ha ha ha ....now that was funny.....sad but oh so true
This old horse has been beaten thoroughly.
A $1.83 per US gallon here and MUCH cheaper at the Indian Res.
Are you kiddin'? The more you beat that horse the tenderer it gets!!!!
Easy, big fella, or I'll fetch Ellymay
